Why AGPL-3.0 (and not a more permissive license)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

book-indexer's default PDF-extraction backend is PyMuPDF (the `pymupdf`
package, https://pymupdf.readthedocs.io/), which is distributed under the
GNU AGPL-3.0. Because book-indexer links PyMuPDF as a required dependency,
the combined work inherits AGPL-3.0 obligations. To keep the license claim
honest and unambiguous, book-indexer itself is licensed AGPL-3.0-only.

A future release plans to introduce a `PdfBackend` protocol with an MIT-licensed
default backend (pdfplumber), at which point the book-indexer core can be
re-licensed under MIT and PyMuPDF becomes an opt-in `[pymupdf]` extra. Until
that abstraction ships, assume AGPL-3.0 governs any distribution of this
package or a network service built on it.

